<subSubSection id="33CF848BFFFAFFF2A0B6F8C0D8B0F873" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7B6AD700FFFAFFF2A0B6F8C0D8B0F873" blockId="43.[151,1436,1841,2010]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">
We have introduced this genus in 
<bibRefCitation id="1F44AAF1FFFAFFF2A22EF8C3D990F88F" author="Cock" box="[527,732,1841,1866]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Cock" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" pagination="301 - 354" refId="ref30165" refString="Cock, M. J. W.; Congdon, T. C. E. (2014) Observations on the biology of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera) principally from Kenya. Part 7. Hesperiinae incertae sedis: grass and bamboo feeders. Zootaxa, 3872 (4), 301 - 354. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3872.4.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Cock 
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFAFFF2A271F8C0D9CDF88F" box="[592,641,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="CD1DC527FFFAFFF2A2B6F8C0D998F88F" box="[663,724,1842,1866]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, where its split from 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFAFFF2A3E7F8C3DF63F88F" authorityName="Holland" authorityYear="1896" box="[966,1071,1841,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Caenides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFAFFF2A3E7F8C3DF63F88F" box="[966,1071,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Caenides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is discussed. Of the nine species in the genus, a single species, 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFAFFF2A1C5F8A4D9CEF8A8" authority="Evans" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1937" box="[484,642,1877,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lissa">
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFAFFF2A1C5F8A4D979F8AB" box="[484,565,1877,1902]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. lissa</emphasis>
Evans
</taxonomicName>
, has been reared from 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFAFFF2A35DF8A4D8A0F8A8" box="[892,1004,1878,1901]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFAFFF2A35DF8A4D8A0F8A8" box="[892,1004,1878,1901]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Dracaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is treated here. However, its male genitalia are so different from those of other larger members of the genus apart from 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFAFFF2A46DF888DE56F857" authority="(Plotz)" authorityName="Plotz" baseAuthorityName="Plotz" box="[1100,1306,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luehderi">
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFAFFF2A46DF888DF8AF857" box="[1100,1222,1913,1938]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. luehderi</emphasis>
(Pl√∂tz)
</taxonomicName>
(food plant unknown), that it is probably not congeneric (T.B. Larsen pers. comm. 
<number id="CD1DC527FFFAFFF2A392F86CD8BCF873" box="[947,1008,1950,1974]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" value="2014.0">2014</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="33CF848BFFFAFFF5A0E6F833D80FFED8" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="345" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" type="description">
<paragraph id="7B6AD700FFFAFFF5A0E6F833D80FFED8" blockId="43.[151,1436,1841,2010]" lastBlockId="44.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="345" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">
The early stages and food plants of relatively few species of the other 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFAFFF2A3D1F830DF7AF81C" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1937" box="[1008,1078,1986,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFAFFF2A3D1F830DF7AF81C" box="[1008,1078,1986,2009]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Leona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. are known as yet, and the records include palms (
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFDFFF5A1BAFF6AD95FFF75" authorityName="von Berchtold &amp; J.Presl" authorityYear="1820" box="[411,531,152,176]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Arecaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFDFFF5A270FF65D9B8FF75" authorityName="Martinov" authorityYear="1820" box="[593,756,151,176]" class="Liliopsida" family="Zingiberaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Zingiberaceae</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFDFFF5A2DFFF6BDF03FF75" authority="(Hewitson)" authorityName="Hewitson" baseAuthorityName="Hewitson" box="[766,1103,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maracanda">
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFDFFF5A2DFFF6BD887FF75" box="[766,971,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="345">Leona maracanda</emphasis>
(Hewitson)
</taxonomicName>
has been reared from a rattan palm, 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFDFFF5A0FCFF4EDA3EFF10" box="[221,370,188,213]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Eremospatha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFDFFF5A0FCFF4EDA3EFF10" box="[221,370,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="345">Eremospatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., in western 
<collectingCountry id="03C29790FFFDFFF5A200FF4ED93BFF10" box="[545,631,188,213]" name="Zambia" pageId="44" pageNumber="345">Zambia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1F44AAF1FFFDFFF5A2A4FF4ED809FF11" author="Cock" box="[645,837,188,213]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Cock" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" pagination="301 - 354" refId="ref30165" refString="Cock, M. J. W.; Congdon, T. C. E. (2014) Observations on the biology of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera) principally from Kenya. Part 7. Hesperiinae incertae sedis: grass and bamboo feeders. Zootaxa, 3872 (4), 301 - 354. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3872.4.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Cock 
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFDFFF5A2E8FF4FD9B5FF10" box="[713,761,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="345">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number id="CD1DC527FFFDFFF5A329FF4ED809FF11" box="[776,837,188,212]" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFDFFF5A376FF4FDF7AFF11" authority="Evans" authorityName="Evans" box="[855,1078,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halma">
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFDFFF5A376FF4FD8A6FF10" box="[855,1002,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="345">Leona halma</emphasis>
Evans
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFDFFF5A4DCFF4EDED7FF10" authorityName="Martinov" authorityYear="1820" box="[1277,1435,188,213]" class="Liliopsida" family="Zingiberaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Zingiberaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1F44AAF1FFFDFFF5A0BFFF2DDA0FFF3D" author="Kielland" box="[158,323,223,248]" firstAuthor="Kielland" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" refId="ref31481" refString="Kielland, J. (1990) Butterflies of Tanzania. Hill House, Melbourne, 363 pp." type="book" year="1990">
Kielland 
<number id="CD1DC527FFFDFFF5A129FF12DA0FFF3D" box="[264,323,224,248]" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1F44AAF1FFFDFFF5A16FFF2DD958FF3D" author="Heath" box="[334,532,223,248]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Heath" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" refId="ref30712" refString="Heath, A., Newport, M. A. &amp; Hancock, D. (2002) The Butterflies of Zambia. African Butterfly Research Institute and The Lepidopterists' Society of Africa, Nairobi, 137 pp. + CD." type="book" year="2002">
Heath 
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFDFFF5A1B8FF13DA87FF3D" box="[409,459,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="345">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number id="CD1DC527FFFDFFF5A1F8FF12D958FF3D" box="[473,532,224,248]" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1F44AAF1FFFDFFF5A23EFF2DD9B4FF3D" author="Vande weghe" box="[543,760,223,248]" firstAuthor="Vande weghe" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" refId="ref33088" refString="Vande weghe, G. R (2010) Papillons du Gabon. Wildlife Conservation Society, Libreville, Gabon, 424 pp." type="book" year="2010">
Vande weghe 
<number id="CD1DC527FFFDFFF5A29CFF12D9B4FF3D" box="[701,760,224,248]" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1F44AAF1FFFDFFF5A325FF2DD88FFF3D" author="Cock" box="[772,963,223,248]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Cock" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" pagination="301 - 354" refId="ref30165" refString="Cock, M. J. W.; Congdon, T. C. E. (2014) Observations on the biology of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera) principally from Kenya. Part 7. Hesperiinae incertae sedis: grass and bamboo feeders. Zootaxa, 3872 (4), 301 - 354. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3872.4.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Cock 
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFDFFF5A367FF13D834FF3D" box="[838,888,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="345">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number id="CD1DC527FFFDFFF5A3A7FF12D88FFF3D" box="[902,963,224,248]" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="1F44AAF1FFFDFFF5A3F7FF2DDFE6FF3D" author="Heath" box="[982,1194,223,248]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Heath" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" refId="ref30712" refString="Heath, A., Newport, M. A. &amp; Hancock, D. (2002) The Butterflies of Zambia. African Butterfly Research Institute and The Lepidopterists' Society of Africa, Nairobi, 137 pp. + CD." type="book" year="2002">
Heath 
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFDFFF5A401FF13DF1EFF3D" box="[1056,1106,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="345">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="CD1DC527FFFDFFF5A446FF12DFEEFF3D" box="[1127,1186,224,248]" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
suggest that the food plant of 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFDFFF5A0D5FEF7DAAFFED9" authority="Evans" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1937" box="[244,483,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="leonora" subSpecies="dux">
<emphasis id="49A10B12FFFDFFF5A0D5FEF7DAD5FED8" box="[244,409,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="345">L. leonora dux</emphasis>
Evans
</taxonomicName>
is possibly also 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5AC83FFFDFFF5A2BCFEF6D873FED8" authorityName="Martinov" authorityYear="1820" box="[669,831,260,285]" class="Liliopsida" family="Zingiberaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="44" pageNumber="345" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Zingiberaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
